Short answer: Biome can’t prefer or rewrite import specifiers to aliases. It only organizes/sorts what’s already there.

Use your editor’s TypeScript import preferences instead. For VS Code, add:

```jsonc
// .vscode/settings.json
{
  "typescript.preferences.importModuleSpecifier": "non-relative",
  "javascript.preferences.importModuleSpecifier": "non-relative"
}
```

That makes auto-imports use `@/…` when possible (since your `@/*` path mapping exists). If you want existing imports rewritten, you’ll need a separate refactor/codemod or manual change; Biome won’t do that.

